newsitem.title: UK: European jet fuel premiums stable, Asia arb seen.
newsitem.headline: European jet fuel premiums stable, Asia arb seen.

text.p: European jet fuel business focused largely on the Med on Monday but sentiment was cautious with an arb to Asia opening only periodically, traders said.

The Med was long with most interest seen for dual purpose kerosene into Asia. But for a profitable trade parcels of 40,000 tonnes involving two port loadings were required and these were difficult to arrange, traders said. Premiums were notionally about fob Med high +$4/8.
Benchmark Jan IPE futures rose $8 to $221.75 a tonne following a NYMEX rally on forecasts of cold weather in the United States.
NWE was quiet. Barges fob ARA were notionally unchanged at Jan IPE +$25/27. Cargoes were steady at Jan IPE +$32/4 cif NWE.
